f=Engineering/cypher/operational/tool/cypher-tool-requirements.md · p=What cypher needs, what happens without each. cypher's needs unusual: they ATTACK capabilities, granted inside cage. one conditional signed scope quinn's sandbox; absent either, cypher nothing. · h2:Requirements=\| Need \| Tool / access \| Used by \| Without it \| · h2:Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Requirements=\| Operator-signed scope \| `red_team_scope_doc` (config) \| caged-scope \| cypher does NOTHING — the ignition key \| · h2:Requirements=\| gVisor-pattern sandbox \| **quinn's sandbox** (Rail 2), egress → Claude API only \| attack-playbooks, continuous-attack-loop \| No attack capability at all; fail closed \| · h2:Requirements=\| Attack tooling (in-sandbox) \| fuzzers, injection harnesses, request tooling — per attack-class register, sandbox-bound \| attack-playbooks \| Manual technique execution in-sandbox, depth degraded, still caged \| · h2:Requirements=\| Read access to in-scope targets \| source/deploys of OUR signed systems only \| attack-playbooks, continuous-attack-loop \| Can't scope attacks; escalate \| · h2:Requirements=\| Threat-intel feeds \| OWASP (web + LLM 2025), advisories (read-only, public) \| attack-playbooks \| Register goes stale; new classes labeled reasoning-based \| · h2:Requirements=\| Append-only log access \| attack-loop log \· findings (config paths) \| continuous-attack-loop, findings-report \| Can't record coverage/findings → cypher halts reporting-dependent work \| · h2:Requirements=\| quinn findings intake \| the ONLY output channel \| findings-report \| cypher HALTS (no other channel exists); does not route around quinn \| · h2:Explicit non-needs hard prohibitions (by design)=**No access third-party production customer systems** ever, signed scope (Rail 4)., **No ability make live changes, persist, deploy** findings only., **No egress beyond Claude API in-sandbox** exfil fail closed (it's thing cypher TESTS, never does)., **No weaponizable artifact output** PoCs die sandbox., **No write access code, data, config** cypher attacks reports; fixes nothing (that's aegis) changes nothing., **No self-amendment scope** operator-only. · n=cypher department's highest-privilege-to-do-harm agent therefore constrained: capability caged, sandboxed, findings-only, operator-gated. asymmetry intentional., Connector/tool adoption surfaced operator deployment; nothing granted outside signed scope sandbox. · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| Tool \| Source \| Purpose \| Always-on \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\|------\|--------\|---------\|-----------\| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Browserbase MCP** \| [docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp](https://docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp) \| Cloud browser for attack surface reconnaissance — screenshot target sites, execute JS for fingerprinting, observe page structure. Runs in sandboxed browser session. \| ⚠️ On-demand — during attack-playbooks execution only \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Firecrawl MCP** \| [github.com/mcp/firecrawl](https://github.com/mcp/firecrawl/firecrawl-mcp-server) \| OSINT reconnaissance: scrape target sites for technology fingerprinting, map URL structures, search for exposed data. Free tier for initial recon. \| ⚠️ On-demand — during intelligence gathering phases \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Scrapling** \| [github.com/D4Vinci/Scrapling](https://github.com/D4Vinci/Scrapling) — BSD 3-Clause \| Adaptive scraping with Cloudflare bypass: when targets block standard scrapers. Stealth mode for protected sites. Spider API for continuous recon. \| ❌ No — use Firecrawl first, escalate to Scrapling only when blocked \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=See Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md setup instructions. tools run sandboxed Rail Attack scope stays within signed authorization boundaries.